The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval tasks involving images and text, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed framework is based on deep learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of label prediction and semi-supervised learning, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
